bib_record.title: The elastic scattering of 33 MeV 3He particles from 58,60,62,64Ni, 63,65Cu and 64,66,68Zn.

free_txt: Two detector telescopes, with a fixed
angular separation of 5+-0.02 degr., were mounted on
two independent radial arms.Tantalum apertures in front
of each telescope limited the angular acceptance and
solid angle to +-0.31 degr. and 8.0*10**-5 sr,
respectively. Each telescope consisted of a dE-E pair
of silicon surface barrier detectors, typically 0.1 mm
and 1.0 mm   thick, which were cooled to 0 degr. C.
Relative errors are estimated to be typically less than
1.5% for angle<=60 degr., less than 5% for angle >=60
and <=110 degr. and for angle >=110 degr. are in the
range 5-20%. The areal densities of the targets could
not be obtained to better than about 10% because of
non-uniformities in the target foils.
